WEBVTT

00:01.604 --> 00:03.324
Previously, on "Smash".

00:03.402 --> 00:05.320
All:
♪ let's be bad.

00:05.371 --> 00:08.656
- Am I late?
- No, Karen was early.

00:08.707 --> 00:10.692
I'm pretty good
with a computer,

00:10.726 --> 00:12.377
if you need some help.

00:12.411 --> 00:15.213
- What are the charges?
- Loitering for drugs.

00:15.247 --> 00:16.948
♪ When you hear
the things... ♪

00:16.966 --> 00:19.334
You humiliate me
when you're not ignoring me!

00:19.368 --> 00:23.388
I have a pretty clear sense
of what I bring to the party.

00:23.422 --> 00:25.773
- I'm Tom.
- I'm Sam.

00:25.808 --> 00:28.560
Well, I know
what I bring to the party.

00:32.430 --> 00:35.250
♪ Some like it hot,
and that ain't bad ♪

00:36.902 --> 00:40.405
♪ her smile and your fantasies
play a duet ♪

00:40.439 --> 00:43.074
♪ that will make you
forget where you ♪

00:43.108 --> 00:46.444
[Voice cracks]

00:48.714 --> 00:52.050
You okay?

00:52.084 --> 00:55.670
Absolutely.

00:55.721 --> 00:57.805
Do you want some coffee?

00:57.840 --> 01:00.008
What time is it?

01:04.530 --> 01:05.980
$7 million?

01:06.015 --> 01:08.883
That's not a lot
for a musical these days.

01:08.918 --> 01:11.069
Well, if you want to
give me $15 million, Ralph,

01:11.103 --> 01:12.737
I won't say no.
[Laughs]

01:12.771 --> 01:14.739
Well, you'll need it
to get to Broadway.

01:14.773 --> 01:17.075
Well, actually,
we're just looking at a workshop

01:17.109 --> 01:18.409
and an out-of-town tryout.

01:18.444 --> 01:20.411
- And after that?
- Ralph!

01:20.446 --> 01:21.663
You called me, remember?

01:21.697 --> 01:23.081
You called me up
and asked me

01:23.115 --> 01:24.866
if you could come over
and talk to me.

01:24.917 --> 01:26.918
Now you're playing
hard to get.

01:26.952 --> 01:30.171
Why are you here
if you're not interested?

01:30.206 --> 01:32.957
- When's the workshop?
- A week from Sunday.

01:32.991 --> 01:35.043
Okay.

01:35.094 --> 01:38.213
I'm not saying I'm interested,
but I am intrigued.

01:38.264 --> 01:43.685
22b comes after 18,
replace 21 with 19.

01:43.719 --> 01:46.271
No,
I have 12 replacing 21.

01:46.305 --> 01:47.889
That was last week.
Don't confuse her.

01:47.940 --> 01:50.024
When do they
stop changing everything?

01:50.059 --> 01:52.026
Five seconds
before the performance.

01:52.061 --> 01:54.812
Oh.

01:54.846 --> 01:57.732
All right,
if we put the fox number here

01:57.783 --> 02:01.452
and then we put
the Johnny Hyde scene here

02:01.487 --> 02:04.289
and then... wait...
The... the...

02:04.323 --> 02:07.792
Yes, Natasha Lytess
scene here,

02:07.826 --> 02:09.544
it will heighten
the progression.

02:09.578 --> 02:11.796
Oh, my God, this isn't
a high-school science project,

02:11.830 --> 02:13.581
- it's a bloody musical!
- No, it's a workshop!

02:13.632 --> 02:15.133
A first workshop!

02:15.167 --> 02:16.884
And people
are coming to see it!

02:16.919 --> 02:18.169
Could we dial this down?

02:18.203 --> 02:20.388
Look, there is
no discernible story,

02:20.422 --> 02:22.757
linear or otherwise,
between pages 7 and 32.

02:22.808 --> 02:24.592
That's not a gap.
That is a black hole.

02:24.643 --> 02:26.477
And if you don't fix it
this week,

02:26.512 --> 02:28.596
we're all going to get sucked
into its tidal force,

02:28.647 --> 02:31.899
and all we'll be left
with is "Marilyn the red dwarf."

02:31.934 --> 02:33.735
Okay, look, there's been
a really crazy situation

02:33.769 --> 02:35.770
at home, okay?
My husband has been out of town.

02:35.821 --> 02:37.272
My son has gotten
into some trouble,

02:37.323 --> 02:39.073
and I've had to be there
for him.

02:39.108 --> 02:40.575
That is great, Julia.

02:40.609 --> 02:43.861
I am thrilled to hear
your oh-so-sad story,

02:43.895 --> 02:46.414
but this workshop goes up in
front of an audience in a week.

02:46.448 --> 02:48.783
Tom here has written
a beautiful melody,

02:48.834 --> 02:50.501
but check it out...

02:50.536 --> 02:52.620
The lyrics are half finished.
Whole song...

02:52.671 --> 02:54.505
- Half the lyrics!
- Tom, it's okay.

02:54.540 --> 02:56.758
No, it might be okay for you,
but it's not okay for me.

02:56.792 --> 02:59.344
He is not using me
or my music as a club

02:59.378 --> 03:01.663
with which to bludgeon
my writing partner!

03:01.697 --> 03:03.965
Got it?

03:05.000 --> 03:11.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:12.691 --> 03:14.859
[Gasps]
Oh.

03:14.893 --> 03:16.811
It's okay.
It always gets a little tense

03:16.862 --> 03:18.279
with a new musical.

03:18.314 --> 03:19.947
No, not that.
It's my credit card bill.

03:19.982 --> 03:23.451
- It's bad?
- $326.38.

03:23.485 --> 03:24.902
You're kidding.

03:24.936 --> 03:26.621
- You're kidding, right?
- Can I see that?

03:26.655 --> 03:28.289
I don't think I've ever
seen one this low before.

03:28.324 --> 03:29.741
Have you ever
seen one this low?

03:29.775 --> 03:30.958
Oh, my God.

03:30.993 --> 03:32.327
I would be singing
and dancing

03:32.378 --> 03:34.162
if I had a credit card bill
this low.

03:34.213 --> 03:35.830
Both: You're singing
and dancing anyway.

03:35.881 --> 03:37.415
- Shut up!
- Get out of my head.

03:37.449 --> 03:41.502
♪ Her smile and your fantasies
play a duet ♪

03:41.553 --> 03:43.504
♪ that will make you
forget... ♪

03:43.555 --> 03:46.174
Everything okay in here?

03:46.225 --> 03:50.228
- Terrific.
- They're ready to start.

03:53.899 --> 03:56.067
Ellis,
what can I do for you?

03:56.101 --> 03:59.237
Derek is mad because
Julia didn't finish a song,

03:59.271 --> 04:00.772
and then Tom
and Julia and Derek

04:00.806 --> 04:02.240
got into a huge fight
over the script,

04:02.274 --> 04:03.858
and Tom stormed
out of rehearsal.

04:03.909 --> 04:05.860
I just thought
you might like to know.

04:05.894 --> 04:08.112
Yes,
I might like to know that.

04:08.146 --> 04:11.749
Uh,
where are you going?

04:11.784 --> 04:14.335
To rehearsal.

04:14.370 --> 04:17.538
[Piano playing
<i>Let me be your star</i> ]

04:17.589 --> 04:21.759
♪ Her smile
and your fantasies ♪

04:21.793 --> 04:24.345
♪ play a duet

04:24.380 --> 04:28.766
♪ that will make you
forget where you ♪

04:28.801 --> 04:30.852
[Voice cracks]

04:30.886 --> 04:31.869
[Music stops]

04:31.904 --> 04:33.955
Sorry.
Sorry.

04:33.989 --> 04:36.607
- I'm so sorry.
- You okay?

04:36.642 --> 04:39.777
Uh, can we just start it
at the end of the bridge?

04:41.947 --> 04:45.616
[Piano playing
<i>Let me be your star</i> ]

04:45.651 --> 04:47.618
♪

04:47.653 --> 04:50.988
♪ Forget what used to be
[Clears throat]

04:51.023 --> 04:54.409
♪ The past is on
the cutting-room floor ♪

04:54.443 --> 04:56.994
♪ the future

04:57.028 --> 05:01.165
♪ is here with me
[Voice cracking]

05:01.199 --> 05:04.752
♪ Choose me!
[Voice cracks]

05:04.803 --> 05:08.039
[Music stops]

05:21.103 --> 05:24.071
[Orchestra tuning up]

05:24.106 --> 05:26.626
SMASH
S01 Ep06 - Chemistry

05:27.103 --> 05:30.603
Sync and corrected by dr.jackson
for www.addic7ed.com

05:34.590 --> 05:37.390
One, two, three, for, five,
that's it.

05:37.471 --> 05:39.439
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight!

05:39.473 --> 05:42.475
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight!

05:42.509 --> 05:45.278
Yeah, well done, guys.
Let's call it a day.

05:45.312 --> 05:47.196
Check over your scripts, please,
get a good night's sleep,

05:47.231 --> 05:51.001
and no one get
so much as a cold from now on.

05:51.952 --> 05:54.153
- Good night.
- Good night.

05:56.156 --> 05:57.991
Shoot.

06:04.902 --> 06:07.370
Listen, I've been having
some problems

06:07.404 --> 06:09.572
with the whole transition
to the breakup scene.

06:09.623 --> 06:11.791
Uh, we can talk
about it tomorrow.

06:11.825 --> 06:13.459
Oh, I don't want to
take up rehearsal time.

06:13.494 --> 06:14.877
Uh, could I call you tonight,

06:14.912 --> 06:17.463
or maybe even right now
we could grab a coffee?

06:17.498 --> 06:19.966
Tomorrow would be best.

06:20.000 --> 06:22.302
Okay.

06:22.336 --> 06:24.804
Did you talk to her?

06:24.838 --> 06:26.255
According to the doctor,

06:26.307 --> 06:29.008
her throat is inflamed
but not infected.

06:29.042 --> 06:31.144
- There are no nodules or polyps.
- Did he give her a steroid?

06:31.178 --> 06:32.845
She has
some prednisone, yes,

06:32.879 --> 06:34.480
but she's hypersensitive
to drugs,

06:34.515 --> 06:36.015
so it's not necessarily
her best first option.

06:36.049 --> 06:37.934
So what are
her other options?

06:37.985 --> 06:39.652
She's gonna try vocal rest
for the night.

06:39.687 --> 06:42.375
- Okay, what are <i>our</i> options?
- Can we postpone?

06:42.376 --> 06:44.187
- Well, that'd be difficult.
- How difficult?

06:44.188 --> 06:46.859
Well, a lot of our investors
already have it on their schedules.

06:46.893 --> 06:48.778
If we postpone,
it sends the wrong message.

06:48.829 --> 06:51.432
Okay, what about our other Marilyn?
Can she do it?

06:51.433 --> 06:52.198
Whoa, hang on!

06:52.232 --> 06:53.833
Yeah, I'd love to hang on,
but I've just found out

06:53.867 --> 06:55.084
I've got to do
an entire workshop

06:55.119 --> 06:56.586
about Marilyn Monroe
with no Marilyn.

06:56.620 --> 06:58.655
- For a day, maybe!
- Oh, I'm sorry.

06:58.689 --> 07:00.123
I wasn't aware
I had an extra day.

07:00.174 --> 07:02.008
Can Karen do it, Julia?

07:02.042 --> 07:03.309
Can she learn the role
in a week?

07:03.344 --> 07:04.877
- I don't know.
- Stop it.

07:04.911 --> 07:06.295
And by the way,
don't you dare

07:06.347 --> 07:07.547
breathe a word
about this to Ivy.

07:07.581 --> 07:09.966
Stress plays a huge part
in all of this.

07:10.017 --> 07:11.267
You've already been leaning
on her too hard.

07:11.301 --> 07:13.186
If she finds out
you want to replace her,

07:13.220 --> 07:15.355
it'll make it much worse.

07:15.389 --> 07:17.473
A leading lady
with vocal problems...

07:17.524 --> 07:19.525
No one believes that
even when it's true!

07:19.560 --> 07:21.694
Yep.

07:24.314 --> 07:26.949
So what did he say?

07:26.984 --> 07:28.951
It's inflamed.

07:28.986 --> 07:30.620
Strained more than anything.

07:30.654 --> 07:32.655
It's stress.

07:32.706 --> 07:35.725
He gave you
prednisone, right?

07:35.759 --> 07:38.745
Well, that's good.
That stuff is a miracle worker.

07:38.779 --> 07:40.913
Well, there are
a lot of bad side effects.

07:40.947 --> 07:44.667
Darling, you work
in musical theater.

07:44.718 --> 07:47.470
There are lots
of terrible side effects...

07:47.504 --> 07:49.922
Bankruptcy, alcoholism...

07:49.956 --> 07:51.674
Insanity.
[Laughs]

07:51.725 --> 07:53.426
[Whispering]
Don't make me laugh.

07:53.460 --> 07:55.678
Look, everybody uses
the stuff... don't worry about it.

07:55.729 --> 07:58.598
If it helps,
it's worth it.

07:58.632 --> 08:01.100
Look, I have to go work
on tomorrow's schedule.

08:01.134 --> 08:02.535
If you can't do it,
we'll have to get

08:02.569 --> 08:04.520
the Cartwright girl
to fill in, okay?

08:04.571 --> 08:07.573
I can't just waste the day.

08:11.361 --> 08:14.363
[Door closes]

08:23.791 --> 08:26.159
[Sighs]

08:28.762 --> 08:30.430
Would you have to learn
the dances?

08:30.464 --> 08:32.381
- I don't know yet.
- Can you ask?

08:32.433 --> 08:34.549
Not until they ask me.

08:34.601 --> 08:37.169
They better do it fast.

08:39.106 --> 08:41.941
You know what?

08:41.975 --> 08:45.611
I can do this.

09:06.200 --> 09:07.166
Mom.

09:07.200 --> 09:09.469
Mom!

09:09.503 --> 09:11.220
Oh!

09:11.255 --> 09:14.474
Sorry. Aah!

09:14.508 --> 09:16.476
I'm so not
the cook around here.

09:16.510 --> 09:18.811
No kidding.

09:21.348 --> 09:22.849
Okay.

09:22.883 --> 09:25.234
Most of them are...
are okay.

09:25.269 --> 09:26.769
Ow!

09:26.820 --> 09:28.738
Some of them... ouch!

09:28.772 --> 09:30.106
There you go.

09:30.157 --> 09:32.909
They're saved.
I'm saving them.

09:32.943 --> 09:35.278
- Mom, I don't want pancakes.
- You love pancakes.

09:35.329 --> 09:36.996
You burnt them.

09:37.030 --> 09:39.081
Will, can you please put
your phone away?

09:39.116 --> 09:42.251
Why, so I can eat
your bad pancakes?

09:42.286 --> 09:44.287
Look, I know that I'm not
as good a cook as dad.

09:44.338 --> 09:45.588
Yeah, you're not,

09:45.622 --> 09:47.974
which would be
why I asked for cereal.

09:48.008 --> 09:49.125
You're cooking.
[Door closes]

09:49.176 --> 09:50.126
It smells good.

09:50.160 --> 09:51.711
- Dad?
- Frank?

09:51.745 --> 09:54.847
I knew there was a reason
I took the red-eye.

09:54.882 --> 09:57.133
Oh, I'm so glad
you're home.

09:57.184 --> 09:59.051
Me too.

10:02.389 --> 10:03.639
[Both chuckle]

10:03.690 --> 10:06.275
God, I missed you.
Look at you...

10:06.310 --> 10:10.229
Handsome,
even after flying all night.

10:10.263 --> 10:12.148
Wow. I should go away
more often.

10:12.199 --> 10:13.616
No, don't.

10:13.650 --> 10:16.536
Yeah, don't.

10:16.570 --> 10:19.038
Hey, there you are.

10:19.072 --> 10:20.740
Hey.

10:20.774 --> 10:24.043
- Did you take it?
- First dose... six pills.

10:24.077 --> 10:26.712
- And?
- I'm... I'm having cold sweats.

10:26.747 --> 10:29.081
I've had a headache since,
like, 4:00 in the morning,

10:29.115 --> 10:31.500
and I-I just
feel so panicky.

10:31.552 --> 10:35.755
- I'm not in good shape.
- Yeah, what about your voice?

10:37.290 --> 10:38.758
Look, Ivy...

10:38.792 --> 10:41.207
I want to protect you in this
situation, but, you know,

10:41.208 --> 10:42.090
if you take the day,

10:42.091 --> 10:45.264
I'm gonna have to get the Cartwright
girl to fill in... You know that.

10:45.298 --> 10:48.484
Oh, I'm fine.

10:48.518 --> 10:51.487
Okay.

10:51.521 --> 10:53.606
Good.

10:57.110 --> 10:59.161
Ladies and gentlemen...

10:59.196 --> 11:00.863
Marilyn is back.

11:00.914 --> 11:05.167
[Cheers and applause]

11:05.202 --> 11:08.921
- She got better that fast?
- She's probably on prednisone.

11:08.956 --> 11:11.090
That drug
is a miracle,

11:11.124 --> 11:12.875
if you don't mind
the mood swings, insomnia,

11:12.926 --> 11:14.627
hair growth, hallucination,
and weight gain.

11:14.661 --> 11:16.178
[Chuckles]

11:16.213 --> 11:18.881
Listen, I just got
a last-minute recording gig,

11:18.932 --> 11:21.183
but I'd booked
a Bar Mitzvah for tonight.

11:21.218 --> 11:22.351
Can you sub for me?

11:22.386 --> 11:23.769
A Bar Mitzvah?

11:23.804 --> 11:25.388
It's actually Ivy's gig.

11:25.439 --> 11:26.806
She gave it to me
two weeks ago

11:26.840 --> 11:28.224
because she was trying
to save her voice.

11:28.275 --> 11:30.476
Ivy's gig... of course.

11:30.510 --> 11:33.613
- It pays $500.
- Oh.

11:33.647 --> 11:36.632
All right, everyone,
<i>Let's be bad.</i>

11:38.118 --> 11:41.787
Just ask Jerry.
No! No!

11:41.822 --> 11:43.906
I'm not gonna ask him
to pay the maintenance

11:43.957 --> 11:46.542
on an apartment
which is already in his name.

11:46.576 --> 11:48.294
He owns the place.

11:48.328 --> 11:51.714
He can pay the maintenance
without my having to beg him.

11:51.748 --> 11:54.000
Listen, I'll have
to call you back.

11:54.034 --> 11:55.651
[Sighs]

11:55.686 --> 11:57.069
[Knock at door]

11:57.104 --> 11:59.555
Excuse me.
Your temp is...

11:59.589 --> 12:01.641
Actually, I don't know
where your temp is.

12:01.675 --> 12:03.592
What is it, Ellis?

12:03.644 --> 12:05.645
I just came by to let you know
that rehearsals are going great.

12:05.679 --> 12:06.729
Ivy took the prednisone.

12:06.763 --> 12:09.732
- She sounds awesome.
- Good.

12:09.766 --> 12:11.684
Do you need anything else?

12:11.718 --> 12:13.602
Do I <i>need</i> anything else?

12:13.654 --> 12:15.972
Yeah.
Do you need anything else?

12:21.111 --> 12:23.079
Jules.

12:23.113 --> 12:24.747
Jules!
Don't walk away.

12:24.781 --> 12:26.949
Break is almost over.
We're about to start.

12:27.000 --> 12:29.285
If you don't talk to me,
I'll make a scene,

12:29.336 --> 12:30.536
and everyone will know.

12:30.570 --> 12:32.154
That got your attention.

12:32.189 --> 12:33.923
What do you want, Michael?

12:33.957 --> 12:35.591
I want to see you.

12:35.625 --> 12:37.510
I'm here right now.
You can see me right now.

12:37.544 --> 12:39.378
- Alone.
- That's not possible.

12:39.412 --> 12:42.214
- I'm not kidding.
- Neither am I.

12:45.018 --> 12:46.852
I can't sleep, Jules.

12:49.690 --> 12:51.557
- We're back.
- Okay, places.

12:51.591 --> 12:54.777
Top of the mambo.

12:54.811 --> 12:57.780
[Playing mambo]

12:57.814 --> 13:01.484
♪

13:05.936 --> 13:07.436
Two bedrooms,

13:07.517 --> 13:09.217
living room,

13:09.992 --> 13:11.876
dining room,

13:11.910 --> 13:15.246
brand-new kitchen...

13:15.297 --> 13:18.266
83rd floor...

13:18.300 --> 13:21.252
And a view...

13:21.286 --> 13:24.672
of the city.

13:24.706 --> 13:26.674
It's stunning.

13:26.708 --> 13:30.478
- We are the first ones in.
- How'd you swing that?

13:30.512 --> 13:33.431
I have access
to Pam Corker's computer.

13:33.482 --> 13:36.017
So, technically,
this isn't available yet.

13:36.051 --> 13:38.269
If you wanted to rent it
under the table,

13:38.320 --> 13:40.321
you wouldn't have to pay
broker's fees.

13:40.355 --> 13:44.442
You boys are very clever.
[Cell phone rings]

13:47.446 --> 13:49.197
Donny.

13:49.231 --> 13:52.166
Yes, the workshop
is next Sunday.

13:52.201 --> 13:54.702
You don't want to miss it.

13:54.736 --> 13:57.505
Nantucket?

13:57.539 --> 13:59.757
At this time of year?
How dreary.

13:59.791 --> 14:04.295
Well, Nathan Lane is coming
and the Nederlanders.

14:04.329 --> 14:07.715
Okay, thanks.

14:07.749 --> 14:09.934
That, uh,
didn't sound too good.

14:09.968 --> 14:14.305
Lemons
into lemonade, Ellis.

14:14.356 --> 14:16.941
So how much?
$10,000.

14:16.975 --> 14:19.477
It's actually
a bargain for this place.

14:19.528 --> 14:20.928
I'm aware, but, uh,

14:20.929 --> 14:24.466
maybe Pam might have
something for a bit less?

14:24.467 --> 14:25.700
In Manhattan?

14:25.734 --> 14:28.786
Yes, on the island
of Manhattan.

14:28.820 --> 14:30.321
Slit or Mini?

14:30.372 --> 14:32.490
Can it be Christmas,
and I get both?

14:32.541 --> 14:34.492
It's a Bar Mitzvah.

14:34.543 --> 14:36.861
Ivy's Bar Mitzvah,
apparently.

14:36.895 --> 14:38.746
Have you actually
ever been to a Bar Mitzvah?

14:38.780 --> 14:40.881
- Have you?
- I'm not hired to sing one.

14:40.916 --> 14:42.333
Look, I used to sing
at weddings

14:42.367 --> 14:43.968
all the time
when I was home.

14:44.002 --> 14:46.220
The song list is pretty much
the same job to job.

14:46.255 --> 14:48.556
- Where is this gig?
- Northport.

14:48.590 --> 14:50.558
What, way out
on Long Island?

14:50.592 --> 14:52.143
Maybe I'm not Marilyn,

14:52.177 --> 14:54.378
♪ but I do have a job

14:54.413 --> 14:56.063
♪ it's a Bar Mitzvah

14:56.098 --> 14:57.898
do you even know
how to get to Northport?

14:57.933 --> 15:00.735
Yeah, Long Island railroad,
then a cab.

15:00.769 --> 15:02.270
I prefer the Mini.

15:02.304 --> 15:05.806
Mm.
Well, Mini it is.

15:07.526 --> 15:10.511
[Slow music playing]

15:10.545 --> 15:12.145
♪

15:17.619 --> 15:19.754
Oh, I can't concentrate.

15:23.792 --> 15:26.377
I kissed Michael.

15:26.428 --> 15:28.379
What?

15:28.430 --> 15:30.965
He came over the other night
when Frank was out of town.

15:30.999 --> 15:33.517
He was drunk.
I tried to get rid of him.

15:33.552 --> 15:36.187
When we went outside
to wait for the car service,

15:36.221 --> 15:37.788
he kissed me.

15:37.823 --> 15:40.725
And you kissed him back?

15:40.759 --> 15:43.027
Big kiss or little kiss?

15:43.061 --> 15:45.696
- Pretty big.
- Julia.

15:45.731 --> 15:49.600
- He sang to me.
- What did he sing?

15:49.635 --> 15:52.036
Donny Hathaway's
<i>A song for you.</i>

15:52.070 --> 15:54.405
Mm. I bet he sounded
amazing on that.

15:54.456 --> 15:56.407
I probably
would have kissed him too.

15:56.458 --> 15:59.093
Oh, you so would have.

15:59.127 --> 16:02.129
- But I'm not married.
- Right.

16:02.164 --> 16:03.748
I love you.
You know how much I love you.

16:03.799 --> 16:05.082
I do.

16:05.117 --> 16:07.301
You have to
figure this out fast.

16:07.336 --> 16:10.171
You have to think
about Frank...

16:10.205 --> 16:12.807
And Leo.

16:12.841 --> 16:14.258
Too much talk about me.

16:14.309 --> 16:17.061
Let's talk
about you, okay?

16:17.095 --> 16:19.647
Tell me
about the new guy.

16:19.681 --> 16:22.583
Uh, good.

16:22.617 --> 16:24.101
I like him.

16:24.152 --> 16:27.955
"Good. I like him."
Simple, positive.

16:27.989 --> 16:30.441
He's having
some people over tonight.

16:30.492 --> 16:32.743
Meeting his friends.

16:32.778 --> 16:35.146
Simple,
positive, and fast.

16:35.180 --> 16:36.781
Right?

16:36.832 --> 16:40.251
Now we're talking.
[Laughter]

16:40.285 --> 16:43.087
Who needs a $20 Martini
from the Carlyle

16:43.121 --> 16:46.924
when you can get a better one
down here for $7?

16:46.958 --> 16:48.626
What's the name
of this place anyway?

16:48.677 --> 16:49.794
The Bushwhack.

16:49.845 --> 16:52.680
[Laughter]

16:52.714 --> 16:55.633
- That's a terrible name!
- I know!

16:55.684 --> 16:58.519
You know, I kind of
love this place...

16:58.553 --> 17:00.604
Old jukebox...

17:00.639 --> 17:02.606
Darts!

17:02.641 --> 17:04.525
Mmm.

17:04.559 --> 17:08.595
I didn't even know
people played darts anymore.

17:09.865 --> 17:10.981
What's this?

17:11.031 --> 17:12.616
Oh, man,
that's the best.

17:12.651 --> 17:14.734
- Yeah.
- <i>Big buck hunter.</i>

17:14.769 --> 17:16.287
How do you play?

17:16.320 --> 17:18.372
[Coins rattling]

17:21.542 --> 17:23.243
So I just shoot me
some bucks?

17:23.278 --> 17:25.796
[Laughs]
Step aside, boys!

17:25.830 --> 17:29.383
[Gunfire and country music]

17:35.340 --> 17:38.309
[Who you are plays]

17:38.343 --> 17:39.943
♪

17:49.771 --> 17:54.041
♪ I stare at my reflection
in the mirror ♪

17:57.062 --> 18:01.365
♪ why am I doing this
to myself? ♪

18:03.785 --> 18:08.556
♪ losing my mind
on a tiny error ♪

18:10.542 --> 18:15.179
♪ I nearly left
the real me on the shelf ♪

18:15.213 --> 18:18.015
♪ no, no, no, no, no

18:18.049 --> 18:21.635
♪ don't lose who you are

18:21.669 --> 18:24.939
♪ in the blur of the stars

18:24.973 --> 18:29.059
♪ seeing is deceiving,
dreaming is believing ♪

18:29.110 --> 18:32.313
♪ it's okay
not to be okay ♪

18:32.347 --> 18:35.366
♪ sometimes it's hard

18:35.400 --> 18:39.036
♪ to follow your heart

18:39.070 --> 18:40.988
♪ tears don't mean
you're losing ♪

18:41.022 --> 18:43.157
♪ everybody's bruising

18:43.191 --> 18:45.543
♪ there's nothing wrong
with who you are ♪

18:45.577 --> 18:49.380
♪ yes, nos, egos
fake shows like whoa ♪

18:49.414 --> 18:52.716
♪ just go
and leave me alone ♪

18:52.751 --> 18:56.637
♪ real talk, real life,
good love, good night ♪

18:56.671 --> 18:58.639
♪ with a smile

18:58.673 --> 19:05.229
♪ that's my home

19:05.263 --> 19:07.414
[sighs]

19:07.449 --> 19:09.233
It's fine.
[Giggles]

19:09.267 --> 19:11.235
It's going to be fine.

19:11.269 --> 19:12.987
You sure?

19:13.021 --> 19:14.588
Because if I were you,

19:14.623 --> 19:17.358
I wouldn't be so sure
of anything.

19:24.199 --> 19:26.467
What the hell was that?

19:32.539 --> 19:34.139
♪

19:45.713 --> 19:47.239
Hi. I'm sorry.
 There was no cabs.

19:47.240 --> 19:49.182
I had to walk from the
station in heels.

19:49.216 --> 19:50.383
- Are you Ivy Lynn?
- Sure.

19:50.434 --> 19:52.719
- You better get up there.
- Okay.

19:52.770 --> 19:54.687
Crap.

19:54.722 --> 19:58.107
Crap.

19:58.142 --> 19:59.392
Hello.

19:59.443 --> 20:00.777
Um...

20:00.811 --> 20:02.312
Welcome to...

20:02.346 --> 20:06.232
Ethan's Bar Mitzvah!
[Applause]

20:06.283 --> 20:10.086
[Sighs]

20:12.323 --> 20:15.959
We were in P-town last summer,
just window shopping for fun.

20:15.993 --> 20:20.246
A house on the beach...
Small, a cottage...

20:20.297 --> 20:22.749
- $2 million.
- That's actually cheap.

20:22.800 --> 20:25.552
But where are you gonna
put your money now, you know?

20:25.586 --> 20:28.171
What can you invest in?

20:28.205 --> 20:29.906
Broadway musicals.

20:29.940 --> 20:33.393
[Laughter]

20:33.427 --> 20:37.397
So how did you meet John?

20:37.431 --> 20:39.983
Our mothers set us up.

20:40.017 --> 20:41.985
- Alicia set you up.
- Oh, stop.

20:42.019 --> 20:44.404
He just came out
to her last year.

20:44.438 --> 20:47.607
[Chuckles]
Last year?

20:47.658 --> 20:50.159
You guys having
a good time, huh?

20:50.194 --> 20:52.946
Terrific.

20:52.997 --> 20:54.998
[Cell phone chimes]

20:58.535 --> 21:01.204
Is everything okay?

21:01.238 --> 21:03.790
I don't know.

21:03.841 --> 21:06.125
Excuse me.

21:09.013 --> 21:10.597
What did you see?

21:10.631 --> 21:13.633
I don't know,
but it was really weird.

21:13.684 --> 21:16.686
Marilyn was in the mirror,
and it was Karen.

21:16.720 --> 21:19.472
Sounds like anxiety
and insomnia to me.

21:19.523 --> 21:21.608
- Sam.
- Yeah, she called me too.

21:21.642 --> 21:22.942
I came right over.

21:22.977 --> 21:24.394
Let's get you to bed, honey.
Come on.

21:24.428 --> 21:26.696
Really,
it just freaked me out.

21:26.730 --> 21:29.482
And the next thing
could be... oh, God.

21:29.533 --> 21:32.318
Oh, God, you bloat up,
and you grow hair.

21:32.369 --> 21:34.487
I'm not kidding...
Like a wolfman.

21:34.538 --> 21:36.122
- A-woo!
- Stop!

21:36.156 --> 21:37.957
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

21:37.992 --> 21:39.826
- D...
- A-woo!

21:39.877 --> 21:41.544
I am...
this is real!

21:41.578 --> 21:43.713
Ivy, baby,
you need to calm down.

21:43.747 --> 21:46.049
- It's nothing.
- It's <i>not</i> nothing.

21:46.083 --> 21:48.418
Look, she's just upset,
all right?

21:48.452 --> 21:51.387
One of the side effects
can be, like, mood changes.

21:51.422 --> 21:54.590
I know.
I've taken this drug before.

21:54.624 --> 21:56.893
Lie down.
Come on.

21:56.927 --> 21:58.061
There it is.

22:01.849 --> 22:03.850
- What did he say?
- It's a text that says,

22:03.901 --> 22:05.268
"might need you tomorrow.
Please be discreet."

22:05.302 --> 22:07.070
- And Tom sent this?
- Yes.

22:07.104 --> 22:09.272
- Did you call him?
- It says "be discreet."

22:09.306 --> 22:11.024
If Ivy finds out,
it could make her worse.

22:11.075 --> 22:12.608
[Whistles]
What's-your-name...

22:12.642 --> 22:14.077
<i>Hava nagila</i> come on!
Oh, babe, I got to go.

22:14.111 --> 22:15.578
Okay.

22:15.612 --> 22:18.581
[Band playing <i>Hava nagila]</i>

22:18.615 --> 22:21.701
♪

22:21.752 --> 22:24.754
♪ Hava nagila,
hava nagila ♪

22:24.788 --> 22:29.592
♪ hava nagila,
hava ♪

22:29.626 --> 22:33.546
[Vocalizing]

22:38.936 --> 22:40.720
Whoo! High!

22:44.274 --> 22:45.744
Ugh.

22:48.178 --> 22:50.947
This scene's a mess.
[Sighs]

22:54.651 --> 22:57.570
What are these?
These are wild.

22:57.621 --> 23:00.790
Periodic table
flash cards.

23:00.824 --> 23:03.242
There is such a thing?
[Chuckles]

23:03.293 --> 23:06.129
Wow,
look at this one.

23:06.163 --> 23:09.365
Bismuth...
That's actually my favorite.

23:11.668 --> 23:14.837
I love that you have
a favorite element.

23:14.871 --> 23:17.090
[Telephone rings]

23:17.141 --> 23:18.641
Hello?

23:18.675 --> 23:20.143
Hey, Michael.

23:20.177 --> 23:21.928
How are you?

23:21.979 --> 23:24.497
We're good.
Leo's great.

23:24.531 --> 23:25.932
Congratulations.

23:25.983 --> 23:27.917
When Julia told me
that you were DiMaggio,

23:27.951 --> 23:31.571
I thought, "perfect."

23:31.605 --> 23:35.591
Well, come over
for a beer sometime.

23:35.626 --> 23:38.394
What can I do for you?

23:43.233 --> 23:45.668
What are you doing
calling me at home?

23:45.702 --> 23:47.837
Because you won't talk
to me otherwise.

23:47.871 --> 23:50.490
You cannot do this.

23:50.524 --> 23:53.676
I have to see you...
alone.

23:53.710 --> 23:56.796
[Sighs]
This is no joke, Jules.

23:56.847 --> 23:59.182
I won't.

23:59.216 --> 24:00.683
I'm going to
the rehearsal space at 10:00.

24:00.717 --> 24:01.968
It'll be locked.

24:02.019 --> 24:04.187
Trust me, I'll get us in.

24:04.221 --> 24:05.638
Artie wants
a story from daddy.

24:05.689 --> 24:07.523
I'm talking to my sister.

24:07.558 --> 24:10.359
Sorry, Suse.
I got to go.

24:14.715 --> 24:16.149
You want me to call Derek?

24:16.200 --> 24:18.785
No. No, no.
[Chuckles]

24:18.819 --> 24:22.038
You know what?
You guys are the best.

24:22.072 --> 24:23.790
Hey, where's
your TV, Ive?

24:23.824 --> 24:26.209
Oh, it's over there
under that pile of clothes.

24:26.243 --> 24:28.911
Oh, you want to
watch a movie?

24:28.945 --> 24:30.213
What do you have?

24:30.247 --> 24:31.831
Are we sick of Marilyn?

24:31.882 --> 24:34.167
Actually,
there's a rangers game on.

24:34.218 --> 24:35.818
Oh, yeah?

24:35.853 --> 24:38.805
What's a ranger?

24:38.839 --> 24:42.625
Okay, I'm gonna go make you
some tea.

24:45.028 --> 24:48.064
Where did you find him?

24:48.098 --> 24:49.849
Like three feet away.

24:49.900 --> 24:51.751
I'm sorry,
but you really are

24:51.785 --> 24:53.536
the straightest
chorus boy I ever met.

24:53.570 --> 24:55.438
- You think I'm straight?
- You're not straight?

24:55.472 --> 24:58.908
I didn't say that.

24:58.942 --> 25:02.245
I interrupted your date.
Was it fun?

25:02.279 --> 25:04.413
It was a cocktail party
with his friends.

25:04.448 --> 25:06.666
Ooh, it sounds hideous.

25:06.700 --> 25:10.203
[Laughs]
It was, actually.

25:10.237 --> 25:12.872
His furniture
is upscale minimalist.

25:12.906 --> 25:16.042
- Blech.
- I know.

25:16.093 --> 25:19.545
[Giggles]

25:19.596 --> 25:22.515
[Band playing jazzy music]

25:22.549 --> 25:24.149
♪

25:32.643 --> 25:33.809
[Scattered applause]

25:33.843 --> 25:35.127
All right, fellas,
last song.

25:35.162 --> 25:36.562
Thank God.

25:36.613 --> 25:38.564
You been checking
that thing all night.

25:38.615 --> 25:40.066
You got boyfriend problems?

25:40.117 --> 25:41.317
Just making sure
it still works.

25:41.351 --> 25:42.368
Okay, you clowns,
um, I get one.

25:42.402 --> 25:43.786
Let's do <i>Shake it out.</i>

25:43.820 --> 25:46.789
It's on the list,
so just follow me.

25:46.823 --> 25:49.075
[Florence and the Machine's
<i>Shake it out]</i>

25:49.126 --> 25:53.296
♪ Regrets collect
like old friends ♪

25:53.330 --> 25:57.383
