♪ ooh, yeah

28:23.513 --> 28:27.533
♪ shake it off

28:27.567 --> 28:30.069
♪ oh, oh

28:30.120 --> 28:32.038
[cheers and applause]

28:32.072 --> 28:34.290
Good job, guys.
Thank you.

28:46.925 --> 28:49.028
[Sighs deeply]

28:49.063 --> 28:50.948
You okay?

28:52.083 --> 28:54.067
Yeah,
my shoulders hurt.

28:54.118 --> 28:56.570
It's just stress.

28:59.574 --> 29:02.042
I'm gonna go for a walk.

29:02.076 --> 29:04.961
Sometimes that...
[Clears throat]

29:04.996 --> 29:08.465
Helps me, uh,
clear my head.

29:10.168 --> 29:11.384
So I'm just gonna, um...

29:11.419 --> 29:12.969
Go for a walk
and figure it out.

29:13.004 --> 29:15.371
Don't stay out too late.

29:22.680 --> 29:24.598
Chicken again, boys.
What a surprise.

29:24.649 --> 29:27.350
- [Laughs]
- Hey, guys.

29:27.384 --> 29:29.653
You're not Ivy,
are you?

29:29.687 --> 29:31.655
Um, no.

29:31.689 --> 29:33.190
I'm Karen Cartwright.

29:33.224 --> 29:35.408
You ever been
to a Bar Mitzvah before, Karen?

29:35.443 --> 29:37.827
No, I'm really sorry.

29:37.862 --> 29:41.414
A friend of mine wants you
to call him tomorrow.

29:41.449 --> 29:44.935
Thanks, guys.

29:44.969 --> 29:48.404
[Phone vibrates]

30:00.351 --> 30:03.370
You got the security guard
to unlock the door.

30:03.404 --> 30:05.822
I told you I would.

30:09.193 --> 30:11.645
Look...

30:14.699 --> 30:18.952
You cannot call me at home.
You cannot text me at home.

30:18.986 --> 30:21.871
You cannot ever again
show up at my home.

30:21.906 --> 30:25.508
I know.

30:25.543 --> 30:27.978
I should have never
let them cast you.

30:28.012 --> 30:31.414
Come on,
I'm pretty good in this.

30:31.449 --> 30:33.300
You shouldn't have taken
the part.

30:33.334 --> 30:35.502
I'm an actor.

30:35.553 --> 30:37.637
Don't offer me the part
if you don't want me to take it.

30:37.672 --> 30:40.006
It was five years ago.
I thought we could handle it.

30:40.057 --> 30:42.392
Yeah, so did I.

30:42.426 --> 30:44.311
We were both wrong.

30:44.345 --> 30:48.932
Okay, um,
you are married with a child.

30:48.966 --> 30:51.167
I have Leo
and Frank, and...

30:51.202 --> 30:53.520
- And here we are.
- And we can't...

30:53.571 --> 30:55.772
Jules, why are you here
if you don't want to be here?

30:55.806 --> 30:59.659
To get through to you.

30:59.694 --> 31:01.845
- You got through.
- Okay, no.

31:01.879 --> 31:04.631
I can't think if you...
If you touch me.

31:04.682 --> 31:07.634
I can't think
even if we don't.

31:11.222 --> 31:13.690
How about we...

31:13.724 --> 31:16.426
Just look?

31:21.666 --> 31:24.517
I so want to see you.

31:26.771 --> 31:30.323
I'll only touch your shirt...

31:33.661 --> 31:35.662
Like this.

32:14.118 --> 32:16.319
You want me to...?

32:30.534 --> 32:33.520
You're more beautiful.

32:35.339 --> 32:38.174
Me?

32:38.208 --> 32:39.676
You...

32:39.710 --> 32:43.480
- Michael.
- No one has to know.

33:14.879 --> 33:16.930
You want me to stop?

33:16.964 --> 33:19.582
No.

33:26.685 --> 33:28.105
♪

33:41.679 --> 33:43.779
Think your friend will be okay?

33:44.182 --> 33:46.900
- Seems like it.
- Good.

33:46.935 --> 33:49.603
Well, my friends
liked you a lot.

33:49.654 --> 33:51.905
[Chuckles]
I was only there three minutes.

33:51.940 --> 33:55.742
Mm, they found that
very reassuring.

33:55.777 --> 33:57.361
They thought
I was moving much too fast,

33:57.395 --> 33:58.996
introducing everyone
to each other.

33:59.030 --> 34:00.914
[Chuckles]

34:00.949 --> 34:02.833
What?

34:02.867 --> 34:04.918
Look,
I have to ask this.

34:04.953 --> 34:09.289
Did you just come out
to your mother last year?

34:09.340 --> 34:11.792
Aaron told you that.

34:11.842 --> 34:14.210
- What a jerk.
- No.

34:14.245 --> 34:15.929
No, he's a total jerk.

34:15.964 --> 34:18.181
I did come out
to my mother last year.

34:18.216 --> 34:21.275
I also came out to her when I was 8

34:21.275 --> 34:22.936
and when I was 12

34:22.971 --> 34:26.607
and when I was 23
and last year.

34:26.641 --> 34:29.393
And don't get me wrong.
You'll love my mother.

34:29.427 --> 34:31.311
She's really nice, just...

34:31.362 --> 34:34.614
A little hard of hearing.

34:34.649 --> 34:36.984
Got it.

34:43.574 --> 34:45.159
- Hey.
- Hey.

34:45.210 --> 34:47.978
- How's the voice today?
- "The voice"?

34:48.012 --> 34:50.130
The voice is fine.

34:50.165 --> 34:51.380
Terrific.

34:51.416 --> 34:54.551
Do you want to know
how I am?

34:54.585 --> 34:57.337
- Sure.
- I'm fine.

34:57.388 --> 35:00.140
Tom and Sam came by
and took care of me.

35:00.175 --> 35:03.343
They were worried about me,
because they love me.

35:03.394 --> 35:05.646
And now
you're feeling better, yes?

35:05.680 --> 35:08.599
Yes, I am.

35:11.469 --> 35:13.237
Wonderful.

35:22.313 --> 35:24.665
Karen...

35:24.699 --> 35:26.366
Sorry about
the confusing texts.

35:26.417 --> 35:27.784
Oh, I'm just glad
you thought of me.

35:27.818 --> 35:29.419
- Thanks.
- Great.

35:29.454 --> 35:34.091
Oh, and if anything else
happens, I'm ready.

35:34.125 --> 35:35.175
Karen...

35:35.210 --> 35:37.878
So how'd it go?

35:37.929 --> 35:40.180
Maybe I'm not cut out
for Bar Mitzvahs.

35:40.215 --> 35:42.849
Did you at least
get a good tip?

35:42.884 --> 35:45.135
Uh...

35:45.169 --> 35:47.221
Oh, well.

35:47.272 --> 35:49.306
<i>Oh, well.</i>
<i>Holy cow!</i>

35:49.340 --> 35:50.941
- Holy moly!
- What?

35:50.975 --> 35:53.560
I gave you that gig,
and Bobby Raskin was there?

35:53.611 --> 35:55.195
Who?

35:55.230 --> 35:57.531
Bobby Raskin was
at the Bar Mitzvah you gave me.

35:57.565 --> 36:00.117
- And you gave it to her?
- Who's Bobby Raskin?

36:00.151 --> 36:01.568
Bobby Raskin?

36:01.619 --> 36:03.203
Ugh!
You're from Iowa.

36:03.238 --> 36:06.406
He's big.
He's like Tommy Mottola.

36:06.457 --> 36:08.909
And don't say,
"who's Tommy Mottola?"

36:08.960 --> 36:11.113
[Loud thud]

36:12.964 --> 36:14.298
You okay?

36:14.332 --> 36:16.917
That chick
really gets on my nerves.

36:16.968 --> 36:19.052
Why didn't I just have her fired
the first day?

36:19.087 --> 36:21.255
Marilyn would have!

36:22.090 --> 36:24.224
What was that for?

36:24.259 --> 36:26.260
'Cause you're awesome.

36:28.813 --> 36:32.149
Uh, hi. Hello.
Is this Mr. Raskin's office?

36:32.183 --> 36:35.485
<i>I'm Karen Cartwright.
He asked that I call him?</i>

36:35.520 --> 36:37.187
- Hi.
- Hi.

36:37.221 --> 36:39.106
How are you?

36:39.157 --> 36:41.825
Uh...

36:41.859 --> 36:43.910
Good.

36:43.945 --> 36:45.646
You?

36:45.680 --> 36:47.631
Great.

36:50.501 --> 36:53.537
I think
we're about to start.

36:53.571 --> 36:56.456
- And we're in.
- All right, everyone...

36:56.507 --> 37:00.794
Our esteemed lyricist
has finally finished the verses

37:00.845 --> 37:02.629
for <i>History is made at night.</i>

37:02.680 --> 37:04.965
Since we're six days away
from an invited audience,

37:05.016 --> 37:06.450
I'd like to work quickly.

37:06.484 --> 37:08.185
So let's try it
with the original staging

37:08.219 --> 37:09.636
and see if it fits
the new words.

37:09.687 --> 37:11.772
Places for the second verse,
please.

37:11.806 --> 37:14.107
Uh, and if you guys
could try it without the pages,

37:14.142 --> 37:15.108
that would be super.

37:15.143 --> 37:17.110
- Uh...
- Just do it.

37:17.145 --> 37:18.228
No, no, no.
I got it.

37:18.262 --> 37:21.565
- Great.
- All right, then.

37:30.875 --> 37:33.043
[Piano playing
<i>History is made at night</i> ]

37:33.077 --> 37:34.911
[Ensemble doo-wop vocalizing]

37:34.945 --> 37:38.382
♪ I see the questions
burning in your eyes ♪

37:38.416 --> 37:42.219
♪ or is it
just reflections ♪

37:42.253 --> 37:43.587
♪ mm

37:43.621 --> 37:46.890
♪ of the stars
high above you? ♪

37:46.924 --> 37:52.479
♪ Oh, I'm just your student,
and I hope you won't be shy ♪

37:52.513 --> 37:55.816
♪ please make corrections

37:55.850 --> 38:00.737
♪ yeah, on the sweetest way
to love you ♪

38:00.772 --> 38:03.106
♪ Come and sit close...
Whisper close ♪

38:03.140 --> 38:05.909
♪ tell me just when
to say when ♪

38:05.943 --> 38:08.195
♪ Then we'll sleep
through the day ♪

38:08.246 --> 38:09.863
♪ Then whenever you say

38:09.914 --> 38:11.865
♪ that's when school
begins again ♪

38:11.916 --> 38:16.253
♪ 'cause history
is made at night ♪

38:16.287 --> 38:19.256
♪ so close the books,
turn off the light ♪

38:19.290 --> 38:22.175
♪ and listen

38:22.210 --> 38:26.380
♪ let my heart
be the teacher ♪

38:26.431 --> 38:28.715
♪ no one here to disapprove

38:28.766 --> 38:34.938
♪ as we review the lessons
you've been missin' ♪

38:34.972 --> 38:42.479
♪ let the moon
be our only light ♪

38:42.513 --> 38:47.534
♪ 'cause history
is made at night ♪

38:47.568 --> 38:48.902
[Ensemble vocalizing]

38:48.953 --> 38:50.904
♪ Come here

38:50.938 --> 38:52.789
♪ oh, oh, yeah

38:52.824 --> 38:56.126
♪ someday they'll write
lots of books ♪

38:56.160 --> 38:58.628
♪ about our fame and glory

38:58.663 --> 39:02.215
♪ but if all their reports
are just movies and sports ♪

39:02.250 --> 39:05.669
Both: ♪ They'll be missin'
the whole story ♪

39:05.703 --> 39:09.339
All:
♪ Missin' the whole story

39:09.373 --> 39:11.892
both: ♪ 'cause history
is made at night ♪

39:11.926 --> 39:14.895
♪ so close the books,
turn off the light ♪

39:14.929 --> 39:17.397
♪ and listen

39:17.432 --> 39:19.683
[music stops, laughter]

39:19.717 --> 39:22.519
Oh, for crying out loud!

39:22.553 --> 39:24.821
Is it too much to ask
for a moment of professionalism?

39:24.856 --> 39:26.356
Sorry.

39:26.390 --> 39:27.908
[Chuckles mockingly]
"Sorry" doesn't help me.

39:27.942 --> 39:29.826
I need something
that vaguely resembles sex.

39:29.861 --> 39:33.413
Could we try that today
with our Marilyn, please?

39:33.448 --> 39:36.266
I can do sex.

39:36.300 --> 39:39.586
Then I'd like to see it.

39:39.620 --> 39:42.322
And by the way, I'd love it if you
were singing at the same time.

39:42.356 --> 39:44.174
Let's take it
from the bridge, please.

39:44.208 --> 39:47.878
Hey, uh, while we're stopped,
I have a thought.

39:47.912 --> 39:50.430
Maybe you could give me notes

39:50.465 --> 39:53.450
without publicly humiliating me
at the same time.

39:53.484 --> 39:55.435
Oh, great.

39:55.470 --> 39:59.022
Oh, and maybe... maybe you
could remember that artists

39:59.056 --> 40:02.476
are not football players
who can take endless abuse

40:02.527 --> 40:04.110
and still do their jobs!

40:04.145 --> 40:05.445
Okay.

40:05.480 --> 40:07.731
Miss Monroe
is having a moment.

40:07.765 --> 40:11.368
Oh! Well, maybe a different
miss Monroe could do it better.

40:11.402 --> 40:13.153
Miss Cartwright?

40:13.204 --> 40:16.206
Maybe you could take
a crack at it.

40:16.240 --> 40:18.859
- Let's take a ten.
- Um, no, seriously, Derek...

40:18.893 --> 40:20.794
We should have given them
more time with the lyrics.

40:20.828 --> 40:22.546
I don't need
more time with the lyrics!

40:22.580 --> 40:23.797
You know what I need?

40:23.831 --> 40:25.815
I need to stop
sleeping with men

40:25.850 --> 40:28.885
who are complete
narcissistic pricks!

40:30.888 --> 40:33.673
Oh, and you're
not <i>that</i> good-looking!

40:33.724 --> 40:36.927
And you're
not that good in bed either!

40:40.765 --> 40:43.751
It's just a side effect
from the steroids.

40:47.021 --> 40:50.524
[Crying]

40:57.949 --> 41:00.083
[Exhales sharply]

41:00.117 --> 41:02.285
You all right?

41:02.319 --> 41:04.371
Yeah, I will be.

41:07.124 --> 41:10.961
[Both laughing]

41:16.384 --> 41:19.686
Well, that was quite a bit
of unscripted drama today.

41:19.720 --> 41:21.137
I probably
shouldn't say anything,

41:21.171 --> 41:22.556
but I rather enjoyed it.

41:22.607 --> 41:24.274
Ralph!
There you are!

41:24.308 --> 41:27.394
You found the Bushwhack!

41:27.445 --> 41:28.979
This is Ellis and Zach.

41:29.013 --> 41:32.365
Ralph Masius, my favorite
Broadway producer.

41:32.400 --> 41:34.618
- Hi.
- Hey.

41:34.652 --> 41:35.869
Hello.
Could we, uh, have four

41:35.903 --> 41:37.787
of your delicious Martinis,
please?

41:37.822 --> 41:39.406
Done.

41:39.457 --> 41:40.957
Best drink
in town, I swear.

41:40.992 --> 41:42.993
- I'm not fancy.
- I am.

41:43.027 --> 41:44.544
The Nederlanders
are coming.

41:44.579 --> 41:46.546
David stone,
Jeffrey finn...

41:46.581 --> 41:48.632
The list is incredibly
impressive.

41:48.666 --> 41:50.133
- Show him the list, Ellis.
- No need.

41:50.167 --> 41:52.752
- Put me on it.
- Put him on the list, Ellis.

41:52.803 --> 41:54.754
Is that the reason
why we're celebrating?

41:54.805 --> 41:56.923
Well, that and a couple
of other things.

41:56.958 --> 41:59.566
I just landed a beautiful, luxury,

41:59.567 --> 42:01.294
two-bedroom apartment...

42:01.295 --> 42:03.597
Top floor at a basement price.

42:03.648 --> 42:05.432
- Awesome!
- What neighborhood?

42:05.483 --> 42:07.100
The Lower East Side, boys.

42:07.151 --> 42:10.654
I, um, have a nephew
who has a nice building.

42:10.688 --> 42:12.572
[Laughs]

42:12.607 --> 42:14.190
Cheers, everybody!

42:14.224 --> 42:16.610
- Here's to change!
- I'm down with that.

42:16.661 --> 42:19.446
- Mmm!
- Not bad.

42:19.497 --> 42:22.248
How's your
<i>big buck hunter,</i> Ralph?

42:22.283 --> 42:24.367
Buck what-er?
[Laughter]

42:24.401 --> 42:28.755
Come on, follow me.
I'm taking you all on.

42:28.789 --> 42:31.875
Oh, we'd like
four more Martinis, please.

42:31.909 --> 42:34.995
Five...

42:35.029 --> 42:37.964
One for you.

42:38.015 --> 42:40.818
[Coins rattling]

42:42.053 --> 42:43.803
Watch out, now.

42:43.854 --> 42:46.255
It's my turn.

